      "writtenOn": "2020-01-09T19:45:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e i implied that one cannot specify content type or fetch url if they specify a datastream.\n\u003e \n\u003e \u003e Also for GCS, doesn\u0027t GCS allow you to set the content type directly already?  \n\u003e \n\u003e it does. What are you implying?\n\nI\u0027m wondering why the standard HTTP mechanisms for dealing with content-type are insufficient. Is the intended use case for clients to be able to know \"oh, this is an image I should display\" without fetching the artifact? What if the GCS content-type doesn\u0027t match?\n\n\u003e \n\u003e content type is mostly for resultdb clients. We will probably use something more explicit. For BQ export of test results, we explicitly accept BigQueryExports message which explains which test results to export, where to. We can do the same for bigquery export of data streams.\n\nAh, I didn\u0027t see the BigQueryExports message; that makes sense to me.",
      "parentUuid": "8c481f34_76f809ac",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 32,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 26
      },
      "revId": "156067046ce73e87413a6156ba84bbd86c24f191",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
